NAME

    Memoize::HashKey::Ignore - allow certain keys not to be memoized.

SYNOPSIS

        use Memoize;
    
        tie my %scalar_cache = 'Memoize::HashKey::Ignore', IGNORE => sub { my $key = shift, return ($key eq 'BROKENKEY') ? 1 : 0; };
        tie my %list_cache   = 'Memoize::HashKey::Ignore', IGNORE => sub { my $key = shift, return ($key eq 'BROKENKEY') ? 1 : 0; };
    
        memoize('function', SCALAR_CACHE => [ HASH => \%scalar_cache ], LIST_CACHE => [ HASH => \%list_cache ]);

EXPORT

    Sometimes you don't want to store certain keys. You know what the
    values looks likes, but you can't easily write memoize function which
    culls them itself.

    Memoize::HashKey::Ignore allows you to supply a code reference which
    describes, which keys should not be stored in Memoization Cache.

    This module will allow you to memoize the entire function with
    splitting it into cached and uncached pieces.

